latestPosts.caption:
A new chapter in High Jewelry begins with Monili—the first collection co-created by Gucci and Pomellato. Reflecting a shared commitment to Italian craftsmanship and a timeless approach to design, the collection draws on an archival Pomellato creation from 1984 to distill the past into something distinctly present. With softened, continuous lines and sculptural silhouettes, Monili expresses a quiet sophistication, where material, form, and meaning are held in perfect balance.  
 
Art Director: Riccardo Zanola 
Photographer: Philippe Lacombe 
 
#GucciPomellato #GucciHighJewelry
